<plot>Eddie Foy Jr. and his small daughter can't pay the rent and are starving because Foy can't get a job in Hollywood. As a last resort, he makes on more try to get in and see a producer at a studio, and is mistaken for a masseur by the producer. Foy thinks the producer is nuts but decides to play along until he can audition his dancing talent. When he does, the producer thinks he is nuts until Foy reveals he is a performer looking for a job, and calls for a studio cop. During the chase, the producer realizes that Foy is a great actor and offers him a job.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?125516</url></doc>
